{{champion:421}} 
{{champion:161}} 

Of these 15 champs, we have 8 squishies and 7 tanky champs.

All the tanky champs are kitable or deal their true damage through conditional autos only, {{champion:86}}, {{champion:31}}, {{champion:122}}, {{champion:421}}, {{champion:39}}, {{champion:2}} {{champion:164}} 

All of the squishy champs can be easily blown up or have their true damage dodged. 

The few champs with unavoidable true damage are squishy.

However not all of these champs are necessarily dangerous to a tank. 

These champs are probably only {{champion:114}} {{champion:86}} (when villain){{champion:29}} {{champion:67}} {{champion:11}}{{champion:122}} (when fully stacked) {{champion:161}} {{champion:164}} ?

Of these champs they are mostly squishy and easily dealt with (insert Vayne joke here), so I don't think tank build optimization is too dire. I'm not including %health shreds because these are mostly done through physical or magic damage, and they start falling off as resistances are built, so they aren't exactly chewing through tanks in a second or two.

However with that said, I wouldn't mind more tank items.

Also, %health damage is a relative non-factor to squishies, as they take the least damage from it.
